Three men were stabbed around breakfast time at a McDonald’s and police are on a manhunt for the suspect. The triple stabbing happened shortly before 7am on Tuesday at the fast food restaurant at the corner of Colesville Road and 2nd Avenue in Silver Spring, Maryland, Montgomery county police said. Police officers arrived at the scene to find two men with stab wounds, according to WUSA. Soon after, another man returned to the McDonald’s to tell police that he had also been stabbed. All three victims sustained injuries that did not appear to be life-threatening, according to cops. The suspect fled the scene before police officers arrived. Cops were searching for a man suspected to be responsible for the stabbings. A description of him was not immediately released. Anyone with information is urged to contact the Montgomery County Crime Solvers. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.